DIDYOUKNOW_MSG34: “We know that enduring peace cannot be bought at the cost of other people's freedom.” --President Franklin D. Roosevelt, January 9, 1941
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG35: “I hate war as only a soldier who has lived it can, only as one who has seen its brutality, its stupidity.” -- General Dwight D. Eisenhower, January 10, 1946
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG36: “It is foolish and wrong to mourn the men who died. Rather we should thank God that such men lived.” -- General George S. Patton, June 7, 1945
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG37: “It was close; but that's the way it is in war. You win or lose, live or die — and the difference is just an eyelash.” -- General Douglas MacArthur, March 17, 1942
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG38: "I have nothing to offer but blood, toil, tears and sweat." -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, May 13, 1940
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG39:
"What is our policy? ... to wage war against a monstrous tyranny, never surpassed in the dark, lamentable catalogue of human crime." 
 -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, May 13, 1940
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG40:
“Let us therefore brace ourselves to our duties, and so bear ourselves that, if the British Empire and its Commonwealth last for a thousand years, 
men will still say, 'This was their finest hour.'” -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, June 18, 1940
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG41: "Never in the field of human conflict was so much owed by so many to so few." -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, August 20, 1940
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG42:
“We shall not fail or falter; we shall not weaken or tire. Neither the sudden shock of battle, nor the long-drawn trials of vigilance and exertion
will wear us down. Give us the tools and we will finish the job.” -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, February 9, 1941
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG43:
“Never give in — never, never, never, never, in nothing great or small, large or petty, never give in except to convictions of honour and good sense. 
Never yield to force; never yield to the apparently overwhelming might of the enemy.” -- Prime Minister Winston Churchill, October 19, 1941
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG44: “In war, whichever side may call itself the victor, there are no winners, but all are losers.” -- Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain, July 3, 1938
DIDYOUKNOW_MSG45:
“It is evil things that we will be fighting against—brute force, bad faith, injustice, oppression and persecution—and against them I am certain 
that the right will prevail.” -- Prime Minister Neville, Sept. 3, 1939
DIVISIONS_AIRBORNE_DESC: Being behind enemy lines is second nature to the Airborne Division. Outlasting the opposition on their territory requires extreme physical conditioning which is stressed to all Airborne recruits. As is the need to keep a low profile, submachine guns outfitted with suppressors enable Airborne paratroopers to stay hidden from enemy reconnaissance.
DIVISIONS_AIRBORNE_RECOMMENDED:
The rapid deployment division. 
Good for intermediate soldiers.
DIVISIONS_ARMORED_DESC: A pile of smoldering rubble is left in the wake of the Armored Division. Clearing enemy strongholds requires a hearty dose of explosives and firepower. Luckily, Armored soldiers are the best supplied on the battlefield.  Standard issue bipods for their machine guns enable the Armored to hold power positions and provide suppressive fire that can turn the tide of the war.

DIVISIONS_ARMORED_RECOMMENDED:
The heavy weapons division. 
Good for intermediate soldiers.

DIVISIONS_EXPEDITIONARY_DESC: At the forefront of the resistance movement, the Expeditionary Force sabotages the enemy’s best laid plans. Midnight raids of ammo depots have left those in the Expeditionary surprisingly well-equipped with enemy tactical grenades. Hand-crafted Incendiary shells for their shotguns help the Expeditionary fighters set the night ablaze as the enemy’s hope goes up in smoke.

DIVISIONS_INFANTRY_DESC: First to the front, the Infantry Division is always in the thick of it. Finely-tuned rifles and excellent marksmanship allow these fighters to outgun the rest. Special training on the use of the Bayonet make Infantry riflemen a threat at all ranges.

DIVISIONS_MOUNTAIN_DESC: Keeping the enemy in constant fear, the Mountain Division strikes when least expected. Unnaturally skilled in target identification, these snipers scout enemy movements and report critical intel that advances the war effort. Extensive practice in meditation has taught these Mountain snipers to block out their surroundings and with Sharpshooter focus precisely pick off even the toughest of targets.

KILLSTREAKS_AIRSTRIKE_DESC: An aerial obliteration bombing that makes multiple passes over enemy occupied territory.
KILLSTREAKS_AIRSTRIKE_HINT: Carpet Bombing will attempt to avoid your location so stay away from enemies when it goes to make a pass for best results.
KILLSTREAKS_AIRSTRIKE_PACKAGE_DESC: Drop care packages instead of bombs close to the chosen site.
KILLSTREAKS_CAREPACKAGE_DESC: A Care Package is delivered on a parachute; it contains a random Scorestreak.
KILLSTREAKS_CAREPACKAGE_HINT: Use the fact that Care Packages draw enemies to your advantage. Camp it up and pick off those wannabe thieves.
KILLSTREAKS_COUNTER_RECON_TEAM_ALREADY_H: Team already has a Counter Recon Aircraft.
KILLSTREAKS_COUNTER_UAV_DESC: A fighter that destroys an enemy Recon Aircraft or Counter Recon Aircraft, or blocks enemy Recon Aircraft.
KILLSTREAKS_COUNTER_UAV_HINT: Counter Recon Aircraft can be used right away to prevent enemies from calling Recon Aircraft, or saved to destroy one after it's been called in.
KILLSTREAKS_DIRECTIONAL_UAV_DESC: Call a UAV that shows where your enemy is facing.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_AIRSTRIKE_BUFF: 4th Bombing Pass & reduced time between passes.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_COUNTER_UAV_BUFF: Blocks enemy Recon Aircraft for 10 seconds longer.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_FIGHTER_STRIKE_BUFF: Strafing Pass starts at a higher altitude and is extended.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_FRITZX_BUFF: Increased turn radius & larger blast radius.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_GRENADIER_BLITZKRIEG_CO: Grenadiers I or Blitzkrieg Basic Training
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_GRENADIER_FOURTH_STREAK: 4th Streak Slot is only available while using Blitzkrieg Basic Training.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_MORTAR_STRIKE_BUFF: Select a 4th Targeting Location & shells arrive sooner.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC2_PLANE_GUNNER_BUFF: Slower fly-through & improved turret with reduced recoil.
KILLSTREAKS_DLC4_CANT_USE_STREAK_WHILE_P: Streak cannot be used with parachuting
KILLSTREAKS_DLC4_ONE_SERUM_AT_A_TIME: Only One Serum At A Time
KILLSTREAKS_DLC4_SERUM_BASIC_TRAINING_DE: Serum which improves weapon handling while active. Serum replenishes over time.
KILLSTREAKS_DOGS_DESC: Called in a pack of attack dogs.
KILLSTREAKS_DOGS_HINT: Follow your pups around and let them distract enemies as you finish them off.
KILLSTREAKS_EMERGENCY_CAREPACKAGE_DESC: Drops three Care Packages from a plane, each containing a random Scorestreak.
KILLSTREAKS_EMERGENCY_CAREPACKAGE_HINT: Be sure to check the round timer before calling in this streak. Don't want to lose your precious cargo because the round ended.
KILLSTREAKS_FIGHTER_STRIKE_DESC: Fly a strafing run in a fighter aircraft.
KILLSTREAKS_FIGHTER_STRIKE_HINT: The Fighter Pilot plane needs a clear line of sight to enemies, so it is best to call this streak in along lanes or over open spaces.
KILLSTREAKS_FIREBOMB_ALREADY_ACTIVE: Only one Fire Bombing Run can be active at a time
KILLSTREAKS_FIREBOMB_DESC: A manually targeted aerial bombing run that leaves lingering flames on its path.
KILLSTREAKS_FIREBOMB_HINT: Since the Fire Bombing Run leaves lingering fire effects, use it to trap enemies in a space or wall them off from entering a territory.
KILLSTREAKS_FLAK_GUN_DESC: Destroy all enemy aerial Scorestreaks and block enemies from using new ones.
KILLSTREAKS_FLAK_GUN_HINT: Save this streak until the enemy has multiple aerial streaks overhead, then call it in and reap the rewards. Flak Guns last for 45 seconds.
KILLSTREAKS_FLAK_GUN_ONE_AT_A_TIME: Only 1 Counter Recon Aircraft or Flak Guns at a time allowed
KILLSTREAKS_FLAMETHROWER_HINT: Don't hesitate. The range is longer than you think and enemies don't stop burning when they catch on fire. Burn it all to the ground!
KILLSTREAKS_FRITZX_HINT: It can be risky, but wait until two enemies are close together then aim towards a point between them and get a multikill with your Glide Bomb.
KILLSTREAKS_MISSILE_STRIKE_DESC: An artillery barrage on a designated location.
KILLSTREAKS_MISSILE_STRIKE_HINT: The Artillery Barrage is great at area denial. Place it on an objective or space you want to keep enemies out of and then have friendlies fill the space under its protection.
KILLSTREAKS_MOLOTOVS_HINT: Crude but effective. Hurl these fire bombs at contested areas to create damaging fields of flames that kill and keep enemies at bay.
KILLSTREAKS_MORTAR_STRIKE_DESC: A precision strike upon three targeted locations.
KILLSTREAKS_MORTAR_STRIKE_HINT: With its multiple target locations, the Mortar Strike can be very effectively used by overlapping its targets to clear out all enemies from a space.
KILLSTREAKS_PARATROOPERS_HINT: Overwhelm the enemy alongside your paratroopers.
KILLSTREAKS_PLANE_GUNNER_DESC: Occupy a B-17G and decimate enemies with its ball turret.
KILLSTREAKS_PLANE_GUNNER_HINT: Use strategy when picking targets in the Ball Turret Gunner.
KILLSTREAKS_RAID_FLAK_DESC: Call in Flak to damage enemy fighters.
KILLSTREAKS_UAV_DESC: A recon aircraft that reveals enemies on the mini-map.
KILLSTREAKS_UAV_HINT: When the enemy team has a Recon Aircraft and can see you on their minimaps, your icon on the minimap will pulse white.

LOOT_MTX2_VOUCHER_DESC_PRO_RANKED_HELMET: Congratulations! You're one of the top 100 players for Call Of Duty: World War II Ranked play season 1. As a reward for your efforts, we've granted you the Pro Rank Helmet. Wear it with pride soldier!
LOOT_MTX2_VOUCHER_DESC_TWITCHPRIMEINCENT: Twitch Prime Members, your Resistance gear has arrived. Redeem this pack for one Resistance Supply Drop, which includes one Resistance item, and a Resistance Bribe, which includes three dupe-protected Resistance items!
LOOT_MTX2_VOUCHER_DESC_WEEKLY: Enjoy a free Resistance Supply Drop, which contains one item from the new Resistance set. Thank you for playing Call of Duty: WWII.
LOOT_MTX3_5_PACK_EPIC_TRIPLE_DESC: Contains 10 Rare Supply Drops and two Bribes. Each bribe contains one guaranteed duplicate-protected Epic Weapon, plus two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_5_PACK_HT2: Midweek Mobilize Sale - Heroic Triple Play
LOOT_MTX3_5_PACK_MON_EPIC_DESC: Contains 10 Rare Supply Drops and one Bribe. The Bribe contains one Epic Weapon and two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_5_PACK_MON_HEROIC_DESC: Contains 10 Rare Supply Drops and one Bribe. The Bribe contains one Heroic Uniform and two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_5_PACK_STARTER_2_DESC: Special Offer! Get 10 Rare Supply Drops and limited-edition Resistance and Winter Siege Supply Drops, plus a 1-hour XP token for a special reduced price. Single purchase only.
LOOT_MTX3_5_SDAC_CAMO_DESC: A Bribe that contains one duplicate-protected Weapon Camo as well as two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_5_SDAC_CHARM_DESC: A Bribe that contains one duplicate-protected Weapon Charm as well as two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_5_SDAC_EP_UNI_DESC: A Bribe that contains one duplicate-protected Epic Uniform as well as two random items.
LOOT_MTX3_VOUCHER_DESC_TWITCHPRIMEINCENT: Twitch Prime Members, file in and get a new uniform for battle! Redeem this pack for one Heroic Uniform Bribe, which guarantees one Heroic Uniform, and two rare supply drops. Now suit up and get out there, soldier!
LOOT_MTX3_WEEKLY_UPRISING_REWARD: Epic Bribe & Epic Resistance Uniform Bribe
LOOT_MTX4_SDAC_HELMET_DESC: A Bribe that contains one duplicate-protected Helmet as well as two random items.
LOOT_MTX4_SD_WM_BRIBE_DESC: One Bribe that includes a guaranteed duplicate-protected item from the Blitzkrieg Event
LOOT_MTX4_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_DESC_T: Congrats! You and the COD WWII community have completed 15,000,000 Orders and Contracts! Here's your first reward. Now get back out there soldier, there's more where that came from.
Congrats! You and the COD WWII community have completed 30,000,000 Orders and Contracts! Here's a special calling card. Don't stop now, the best rewards are still to come.
Congrats! You and the COD WWII community have completed 45,000,000 Orders and Contracts! Here's a special weapon charm. Keep pushing! You've almost reached the final milestone.
Congrats! You and the COD WWII community have completed 60,000,000 Orders and Contracts! Here's a special helmet. Keep pushing! You've almost reached the final milestone.
Incredible! You did it! 75,000,000 Orders and Contracts completed! Here's a special weapon variant exclusive to this event. You've earned it.
LOOT_MTX4_VOUCHER_DESC_ENIGMA_DECODER: This intelligence is for your eyes only, soldier.
LOOT_MTX4_VOUCHER_DESC_PRO_RANKED_HELMET: Congratulations! You're one of the top 100 players for Call Of Duty: World War II Ranked play season 2. As a reward for your efforts, we've granted you the Pro Rank Helmet. Wear it with pride soldier!
LOOT_MTX4_VOUCHER_DESC_TWITCHPRIMEINCENT: Twitch Prime Members, get ready for the ultimate customization pack for battle. Redeem this pack for three bribes that will get you a dupe-protected uniform, a dupe-protected weapon charm, and a dupe-protected helmet!
LOOT_MTX4_VOUCHER_TWITCHPRIMEINCENTIVE_W: Honor and Glory Supply Drop Pack

Your final Twitch Prime reward has arrived! Redeem this pack to get yourself fully equipped for your next battle. With this pack, you’ll receive 5 supply drops that will get you a guaranteed Heroic Uniform, a Weapon Charm, an Epic Item, three Resistance items, and three Winter Siege items. Gear up and move out!
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1_: The only good zombie is a dead zombie and thanks to you there's about 400 MILLION more good zombies in the world today. Here's a special zombie calling card. Now get back out there, the best rewards are still to come.
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER2_: You and the WWII community are really thinning the horde out there. Here's a special weapon charm.. Now keep up the good work, that's 8 MILLION zombies down and 1.2 BILLION to go.
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER3_: Congrats! You did it! 1.2 BILLION zombies sent back to the dirt. This is probably against protocol, but the boys in R&D just finished a prototype Tesla Gun. Keep an eye out on the battlefield; we'll be dropping them in for testing until the end of the event.
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER4_: The tides are turning, 1.6 BILLION zombies are now resting in pieces. Wear this helmet with pride, Zombie Slayer.
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER5_: Good work, Soldier. That's 2 BILLION less zombies knocking at our gates. We've got a special reward for your efforts. This weapon charm will display whatever emblem you have equipped. So go make those kill cams a little more personal.
LOOT_MTX5_VOUCHER_DESC_PRO_RANKED_HELMET: Congratulations! You're one of the top 100 players for Call Of Duty: World War II Ranked play season &&1. As a reward for your efforts, we've granted you the Pro Rank Helmet. Wear it with pride soldier!
LOOT_MTX6_CWLPACK_CWL_DESC: Call of Duty World League Packs are now available. Rep the CWL out on the battlefield.
LOOT_MTX6_CWLPACK_EF_DESC: Call of Duty World League Packs are now available. Rep your favorite CWL teams like Echo Fox out on the battlefield.

LOOT_MTX6_CWLPACK_VITA_DESC: Call of Duty World League Packs are now available. Rep your favorite CWL teams like Vitality out on the battlefield.
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1_: Congratulations! You've won 52 MILLION matches and earned this majestic Canadian Calling Card. Keep your eye on the prize, Soldier; many more rewards to come.
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER2_: 104 MILLION wins! You're nearly halfway there! Please except this regal British Flag weapon charm as a reward. But as Churchill once said, “This is not the end. It is not even the beginning of the end. But it is, perhaps, the end of the beginning.” - so get back out there and fight!
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER3_: 'MERICA! Ehem, sorry... couldn't resist. 156 MILLION wins on the board! Here's a star spangled M1911 to help you hold down some more objectives.
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER4_: 208 MILLION wins! You're more than halfway there! While perhaps not the most practical military headgear, the Fez is certainly rich in tradition. Now slap that cap on and get back out there, you've almost reached your final reward.
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER5_: Well done. You all are living proof that teamwork makes the dream work. Now take this M1 Garand Independent II variant and show your enemies some fireworks they'll never forget.
LOOT_MTX6_VOUCHER_TWITCHPRIMEINCENTIVE_W: Gear up with from the latest Liberty Strike content drop and rep your favorite country on the field of battle. Redeem this Liberty Strike Supply Drop Pack and receive 1x Liberty Strike Bribe, which guarantees one duplicate protected Liberty Strike item, and 2x Rare Supply Drops.
LOOT_MTX7_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1_: Great work, soldier. Way to show them what the Infantry Division are made of. Now it's time to see how well you can adapt to the other Divisions. The best rewards are still to come.
LOOT_MTX7_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER2_: You dug in and fought for every inch. That's what the Armored Division is all about. Let this charm serve as a reminder of that for your enemies.
LOOT_MTX7_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER3_: Another win for the Mountain Division. The only thing better than laying prone and picking off your enemies is soaking in some rays while you do it. Don't forget the sunblock!
LOOT_MTX7_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER4_: The Airborne Division doesn't just crush their enemies, they do it with style. Here's something you can throw on next time you feel like showboating.
LOOT_MTX7_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER5_: Leave it to the Expeditionary Division to crank up the heat in the middle of a summer scorcher. Amazing work, soldier. The Cruiser II is yours. Just try not to burn the place down with those incendiary shells, alright?
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1: Boots off the Ground Calling Card
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1_: Well done, Soldier! It's been raining scorestreaks out there. As a reward, we're bringing jet packs to WWII! Just kidding... but here's an awesome calling card.
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER2_: You've been vaporizing the competition out there. Here's a weapon charm to let your enemies know you definitely do not come in peace.
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER3_: Great work, Soldier. We've got a top secret weapon camo as a reward for you. Just remember, ___________ is of the utmost importance and you shouldn't __________ under any circumstance. That's all we're at liberty to say at this time.
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER4_: If I didn't know better, I'd say the sky is falling. Here's an experimental helmet to protect you from all the chaos.
LOOT_MTX8_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER5_: You've scorched the earth and emerged victorious. Here's a top secret, experimental weapon we seized from the Axis rubble.
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER1_: It's like a proper horror film out there. Watch your back or you'll end up with a knife in it!
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER2_: 20 million melee kills! What mayhem! What violence! Talk about Holiday Spirit! Here's your next reward.
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER3_: Good work, Soldier! You've stabbed and bashed your way to 30 million confirmed melee kills. That's more than half way to your final reward!
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER4_: Nobody wanted to eat these, so we made a camo out of them.
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_COMMUNITY_EVENT_TIER5_: Well, what do you know? You brought a knife to a gunfight and you won. Here's your final reward!
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_DESC_APP_2XP_2H: Congrats! You and your squad have unlocked the latest monthly package from the Call of Duty Companion App.
LOOT_MTX9_VOUCHER_DESC_APP_GENERAL: Congrats! You and your squad have unlocked the latest monthly package from the Call of Duty Companion App.

What are “Cookies” and does Activision use cookies, track IP Addresses, or use other passive means to collect information? 
Activision uses cookies on its websites and other online properties. A "cookie" is a small bit of record-keeping information that many websites and other online properties often store on a user's computer or device in order to anonymously identify it and associate activity with it. Cookies typically do not include people's names, or e-mail addresses. 

When visiting our websites and other online services you can choose whether or not to let us enable cookies. We use cookies to optimize your visit, make your browsing experience as effective as possible, and let you know about offers that we think will interest you. Types Of Cookies

* Strictly Necessary Cookies
	These cookies are essential in order to enable you to move around websites or online properties and use their features, such as accessing secure areas of a website. Without these cookies, services you have asked for, like secure login areas, cannot be provided.

* Performance (or Analytics) Cookies
These cookies collect information about how visitors use a website or online property, for instance which pages visitors go to most often, and if they get error messages from web pages.  These cookies don’t collect information that identifies a visitor. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. They are only used to improve how a website or other online property works. We generally contract with independent research and measurement companies, such as Google Analytics, to provide these services on our behalf and which may also be subject to their own privacy policies.
LUA_MENU_CODA_AGREEMENT_TEXT_100:
* Functionality Cookies
	These cookies allow the website or online property to remember choices you make (such as your user name, language or the region you are in) and provide enhanced, more personal features. These cookies can also be used to remember changes you have made to text size, fonts and other parts of web pages that you can customize. They may also be used to provide services you have asked for such as watching a video. The information these cookies collect may be anonymized and they cannot track your browsing activity on other websites.

* Advertising Cookies
These cookies are used to deliver adverts more relevant to you and your interests. They are also used to limit the number of times you see an advertisement as well as help measure the effectiveness of the advertising campaign.

From time to time, we may use web beacons (or clear GIFs) on our websites or other online properties or include them in the e-mail messages we send you. Web beacons (also known as "web bugs") are small strings of code that provide a method of delivering a graphic image on a web page or in an email message for the purpose of transferring data.
LUA_MENU_CODA_AGREEMENT_TEXT_106:
We use web beacons for many purposes, including site traffic reporting, unique visitor counts, advertising and email auditing and reporting, and personalization. 
We also keep track of Internet Protocol (IP) addresses. An IP address is a number that is used by computers on the network to identify your computer every time you log on to the Internet.

Activision may use and share non-personally identifiable (e.g., anonymized or aggregated) information obtained from cookies with third parties such as service providers or advertising partners. An example of the use of such information would be an anonymous group that we assign to an interest categories or segment such as region, gaming preferences, or a combination.
LUA_MENU_CODA_AGREEMENT_TEXT_107:
We may also share non-personally identifiable information obtained from cookies with third parties such as service providers or advertising networks in order to permit them to provide services on our behalf or to partner with us in selecting and serving advertisements for us or our advertising partners. 
Social Network Sites
If you have signed in to a social networking site, such as Facebook, it may have set a cookie on your device which recognizes you when you view content on our websites and other online properties. These cookies allow you to share content across social media via the use of sharing settings.  See your social networking site’s Terms of Use and Privacy Policy for details. For additional details, please see the Social Media Note below.
More Information

Call of Duty®: WWII game required, sold separately. CP are the in-game currency that can be used in WWII to obtain Rare Supply Drops for use in Multiplayer game mode and Zombies Crates for use in Zombies game mode plus other in-game content.

Not all game items available through Rare Supply Drops.

CP purchased may also be used to obtain in-game content in Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare, Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare® Remastered and Call of Duty®: Black Ops III. Each game sold separately. *Use of CP is not available in all Call of Duty® games and is dependent on functionality and is subject to change. CP will be accessible once functionality for CP is enabled and CP are made available in game.

LUA_MENU_STORE_SEASONPASS_LONG:
Experience the full-scale theatre of war with the Call of Duty®: WWII Season Pass*.

Continue the epic journey with 4 DLC Packs in 2018 that include new and iconic Multiplayer Maps, new chapters of Nazi Zombies and all-new War Missions.

Also includes 'Carentan' Bonus Map!

Carentan, one of the most beloved Call of Duty® Multiplayer maps, makes its return in Call of Duty®: WWII. Fight through the destroyed buildings and fortified streets of this war-torn French town in an all-out battle for a strategic German stronghold. All Season Pass holders will receive this iconic map at launch.

This Season Pass allows you to save money on content. Content can be downloaded in-game or from PlayStation™Store when available.

*Season Pass purchasers receive 2018 Call of Duty®: WWII Season Pass content. Season Pass content is subject to change and may not include all downloadable content available for the game. Do not purchase separately, or you will be charged again.

LUA_MENU_WELCOME_FOUNDER_MESSAGE:
We couldn’t do it without you. Check out the epic new modes and maps (and the unique background and patch waiting for you in Create A Soldier).

Time to get your game on.
LUA_MENU_WELCOME_MENU_MESSAGE:
We are thrilled to give you the first opportunity to play what has been our focus and passion for the last 3 years!

This Private Beta is just a small part of the full Call of Duty: WWII Multiplayer experience available at the worldwide release on November 3rd.

Your time with the game is incredibly valuable, so please submit your feedback via Reddit, our Beta survey, or via our social channels. 

Have fun, and we'll see you online!

---  Sledgehammer Games
LUA_MENU_WELCOME_MENU_TITLE: Welcome and thank you for participating in the Call of Duty: WWII Multiplayer Beta!
LUA_MENU_WELCOME_NOOB_MESSAGE:
On behalf of the entire development team, thank you for playing Call of Duty®: WWII. Sledgehammer Games began development of this game three years ago with a singular commitment to delivering innovation and a new era of multiplayer for you, the loyal fans of Call of Duty.  We have made the biggest fundamental change in the player movement and mechanics set in over a decade and encourage you to explore and enjoy the power of the Exoskeleton, with unprecedented speed, verticality, and evasive maneuvering never before seen in Call of Duty.

Thanks again, and see you online!

Sledgehammer Games
LUA_MENU_WELCOME_NOOB_TITLE: WELCOME TO Call of Duty®: WWII MULTIPLAYER

Good to see you. 

Check out Create A Soldier to see what rewards are waiting for you. Go check that out, as well as the epic new modes and maps.

Time to get your game on.

LUA_MENU_ZOMBIES_BUTTON_DESC: Fight through endless waves of the undead in this classic Co-Op mode.
LUA_MENU_ZOMBIES_CUSTOM_MATCH_BUTTON_DES: Create a custom game to fight the undead alone or with friends.
LUA_MENU_ZOMBIES_DESC: Survive as long as possible against the undead.
LUA_MENU_ZOMBIES_PUBLIC_MATCH_BUTTON_DES: Take on the zombie horde in a public match.
LUA_MP_COMMON_TEST_STRING: This is a test string for MP Common.
MAP_DLC1_PARIS_S2_DESC: French resistance battles rage in the streets of Paris in this classic remake from MW3.  Mid-range engagements through city streets and shops.
MAP_DLC1_PRAGUE_DESC: Battle in Prague, site of the assassination of Reinhard Heydrich by Czech Resistance fighters.  Great Domination matches with ranged opportunities across the river and along the bridge.
MAP_DLC1_RAID_AACHEN_DESC: Fight to free the French resistance leaders and stop a train loaded with munitions and supplies bound for the front-lines.
MAP_DLC1_WOLFSLAIR_DESC: Deep in the forests of East Prussia lies Hitler's Eastern Front military headquarters - The Wolf's Lair.  The treacherous main road is flanked by shorter ranged engagements through the outer lanes.
MAP_DLC1_ZOMBIES_ISLAND_DESC: A sea fortress and keystone to the power of the Nazi Kriegsmarine, this mist-shrouded island hides secrets both ancient and terrifying.
MAP_DLC2_DUNKIRK_DESC: The Allied evacuation from Dunkirk has concluded, but the fight still continues.  Long-range engagements dominate the beach while closer encounters are found more frequently along the boardwalk.
MAP_DLC2_EGYPT_DESC: Join the fight in Egypt as the British battle German forces against a classic Giza backdrop.  Wind your way through cat-and-mouse gunfights among the temple ruins.
MAP_DLC2_HQ_DESC: Axis forces are assaulting the Headquarters.  Fight your way through familiar territory to protect our operations.
MAP_DLC2_RAID_DLC2_DESC: Invade German-occupied Sicily to steal key intelligence for aerial support.  Defeat enemy squadrons to allow Allied forces to reach their targets.
MAP_DLC2_ROCKET_BASE_DESC: Fight in Peenemünde, famous site of the German V2 Rocket facility.  Come prepared for fast-paced battles to control the center rocket.
MAP_DLC2_ZOMBIES_BERLIN_DESC: Berlin is burning, and the power of the final Reich has been laid bare.
MAP_DLC3_MARKET_GARDEN_DESC: Fight off German advances to maintain control of the Allied mansion base.  Set in the Netherlands during Operation Market Garden, this map brings intense tight-quarters combat and gunfights around every corner.
MAP_DLC3_MONTE_CASSINO_DESC: Join the Italian campaign in Monte Cassino.  Nestled below a mountaintop monastery, this war-torn village offers rich verticality with rooftop gameplay and sneaky flank paths along the cliffs.
MAP_DLC3_RAID_DLC3_DESC: Airdrop into enemy controlled Tunisia and secure the Mareth Line to take back Africa.
MAP_DLC3_STALINGRAD_DESC: Survive long-range battles between opposing bases in Stalingrad's snow-covered factory district.  Use strategic overlooks to control the map's center, or duck into the underground sewers to avoid sniper fire.
MAP_DLC3_ZOMBIES_DIG_02_DESC: The Nazi territory of Neuschwabenland hides an ancient secret, a horror buried in frost for millennia.
MAP_DLC3_ZOMBIES_DIG_SRV_DESC: When a man bleeds, the flesh grows weak. When a god bleeds, the world trembles.
MAP_DLC3_ZOMBIES_DNK_DESC: The voyage South is fraught with danger, with U-Boats set to target any new vessels en route to the Antarctic.
MAP_DLC3_ZOMBIES_DNK_SRV_DESC: This ship should have never left harbor.
MAP_DLC3_ZOMBIES_WINDMILL_DESC: With European skies controlled by Nazi zeppelins, the Bureau is forced to use a caravan to reach their port in Malaga.
MAP_DLC4_AIRSHIP_DESC: Battle it out atop a German Airship base high in the Alps.  Gain the high ground in the docked Airship, or engage in closer and mid-ranged combat through the base and along the cliffs below.
MAP_DLC4_FUHRERBUNKER_DESC: Oust German forces from their French stronghold within the Chancellery. Maintain control from courtyard vantage points while engaging in chaotic firefights in the opposing flank lanes.
MAP_DLC4_RAID_DLC4_DESC: Infiltrate a secret German weapons and technology manufacturing facility deep in the forests of Austria to steal and destroy secret technology.
MAP_DLC4_TANK_GRAVEYARD_DESC: Fight through an Algerian mine doubling as a Nazi stolen art/gold stash. Trade fire across a battlefield littered with destroyed tanks, or outsmart your foes from the tops of rocky outcroppings.
MAP_DLC4_ZOMBIES_DESCENT_DESC: Thule awakens, and the deathly throne once again casts a shadow over the kingdoms of men.
MAP_MTX1_CARENTAN_WINTER_DESC: A snowy remake of the classic map from Call of Duty 2.  Street fighting with plenty of elevated overwatch positions.
MAP_MTX3_5_SHIPMENT_DESC: The frenetic classic from Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare, brought to life for Call of Duty WWII as a shipment area on Normandy beach.
MAP_MTX5_HOUSE_DESC: Fight for control of an abandoned house, deep in the forest near Mittelberg, Germany.  Beware the horde that comes at night...
MAP_MTX7_DOGFIGHT_EGYPT_DESC: Fly above the classic Giza backdrop. Use the pyramids to your advantage as you eliminate the enemy air defense.
MAP_MTX7_DOGFIGHT_MOUNTAIN_DESC: Soar through the Crimean Mountains as you dodge enemy fighters. The beautiful mountain tops present the perfect backdrop to aerial combat.
MAP_MTX7_SANDBOX_DESC: Tiny soldiers in a big war. Your childhood dreams in the form of a Call of Duty map.
MENU_1_BOMB_IN_THE_CENTER: 1 bomb in the center of the map.  Grab it and destroy the enemy objective!

MENU_TUTORIAL_ACCEPTING_ORDERS_DESC: You may hold up to 3 daily Orders and 3 weekly Orders. There is no time limit for completing Orders.
MENU_TUTORIAL_BTRAINING_1_DESC: From the Soldier tab, choose Divisions to explore your loadout customization options and equip new weapons, Divisions, and Basic Trainings.
MENU_TUTORIAL_BTRAINING_2_DESC: Here you can find and customize the Division loadouts that you'll be taking into battle. You will unlock more custom slots as you progress.
MENU_TUTORIAL_BTRAINING_3A_DESC: Your Division is the central component of your loadout. You can spend Rank Unlock Tokens to access other Divisions, or continue to pursue a career in your current Division.
MENU_TUTORIAL_BTRAINING_3B_DESC: There are a large number of weapons that you will be able to unlock and equip, each of which with its own characteristics. Don't forget that you have access to unique Division skills when you choose to wield the primary weapon class for your Division.
MENU_TUTORIAL_BTRAINING_3C_DESC: Basic Trainings allow you to hone in on the play style you prefer for your loadout. Select the slot now to equip a new Basic Training.
MENU_TUTORIAL_COLLECTIONS_DESC: Collections give truly special rewards when you've collected or purchased all items in a given collection.
MENU_TUTORIAL_CONTRACTS_DESC: Contracts are purchasable, time-sensitive challenges that yield higher quality rewards.
MENU_TUTORIAL_CURRENCIES_DESC: All of your currencies can be found here. Armory Credits can be used to purchase Collection items and Contracts, and are earned through Supply Drops.
MENU_TUTORIAL_DAILY_WEEKLY_ORDERS_DESC: Report to Major Marcus Howard on a daily basis to receive your orders and get the highest amount of rewards.
MENU_TUTORIAL_DIVISIONS_DESC: Your Division loadouts are the most critical element to winning the fight.
MENU_TUTORIAL_DIVISION_PRESTIGE_DESC:
Level up and prestige Divisions to gain access to unique Weapons, Basic Trainings, Uniforms and more.

Be sure to prestige at least 5 Divisions...
MENU_TUTORIAL_DOSSIER_DESC: Access your Combat Record and personalization tools in the Dossier tab.
MENU_TUTORIAL_FINDMATCH_DESC: Press ^3&&1^7 to use the navigation bar at the top of your Soldier Screen to access the Lobby.
MENU_TUTORIAL_HEADQUARTERS_ACCESS_DESC: You can access Headquarters at any time with the press of a button. This will not remove you from any active match lobbies.
MENU_TUTORIAL_HQ_DESC: Stop by Headquarters regularly to access all of your Collections, Daily and Weekly orders, Payroll, and more while spending time with other players on the base. Meet up with your squad at HQ then get back in the fight.
MENU_TUTORIAL_INBOX_DESC: Periodically, you will receive rewards, special items, and messages in your Inbox. Be sure to keep an eye out for new deliveries.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OBJECTIVES_AND_REWARDS_DES: Each Order states what is required to complete it, and the reward you will receive once you redeem it in your Orders Inventory.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OPEN_SOLDIERSCREEN_DESC: You can press [{togglemenu}] at any time to access the Lobby and your Soldier Screen. Open the Soldier Screen now to equip a new Basic Training.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_A_D: Division Level I Skills (like the SMG Suppressor) are no longer tied to a particular Division and can be equipped via attachment slots. Each Division has a new passive ability that fits its playstyle as Level I.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_B: ALL LOADOUTS NOW HAVE 3 PRIMARY ATTACHMENTS
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_B_D: All benefits the Primed Basic Training previously offered are now standard on all loadouts and Primed is removed from the game entirely.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_C: ALL LOADOUTS NOW HAVE A LETHAL & TACTICAL
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_C_D: Now all players can equip a piece of both Lethal and Tactical Equipment. This should encourage usage of Tactical Equipment and create an additional layer of strategy.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_D: ALL LOADOUTS NOW CAN TAKE LAUNCHERS
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_D_D: Now Launchers can be selected without a Basic Training. The Launched Basic Training has changed to accommodate this.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_BASICTRAINING_E_D: With these sweeping changes, a number of Basic Trainings have adjusted functionality and a couple have been removed. Be sure to review the updated list of Trainings.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_DIVISIONS_DESC: Each Division has a new passive ability that fits its playstyle as Level I. Previous Division Level I Skills (like the SMG Suppressor) are no longer tied to a particular Division and can be equipped via attachment slots.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_LOADOUTS_A_DESC: All players now have unlimited sprint stamina. This change should improve the flow and pace of combat.
MENU_TUTORIAL_OVERHAUL_LOADOUTS_B_DESC: More flexibility exists with Divisions, Attachments, Equipment and Launchers. Be sure to review your loadouts as they may have changed.
MENU_TUTORIAL_PAYROLL_DESC: Command will pay your wages in Armory Credits, which you can use to outfit yourself with the best gear available. Stop by on a regular basis to make the most of Headquarters Post.
MENU_TUTORIAL_QUARTERMASTER_DESC: The Quartermaster is your one-stop-shop for gear, weapons, and all other types of loot.
MENU_TUTORIAL_SCORESTREAKS_DESC: Equip Scorestreaks to turn the tide of battle with heavy firepower.
MENU_TUTORIAL_SOLDIER_STATS_DESC: Here you can find information about your current rank and combat performance.
MENU_TUTORIAL_SOLDIER_TAB: WELCOME TO CALL OF DUTY: WWII
MENU_TUTORIAL_SOLDIER_TAB_DESC: The Soldier tab is where you'll customize your character, prepare your loadouts, review your combat record, and personalize your experience.
MENU_TUTORIAL_SUPPLY_DROPS_DESC: You can directly purchase Rare Supply Drops at any time with CoD Points.
MENU_TUTORIAL_V2_ROCKET_1_DESC: Prestige any 5 Divisions at least once to gain access to the V2 Rocket Killstreak.
MENU_TUTORIAL_V2_ROCKET_2_DESC: You are on your way to earning the V2 Rocket. Once you've prestiged at least 5 Divisions you will gain access to the 25-Killstreak.
MENU_TUTORIAL_V2_ROCKET_3_DESC:
Congratulations Soldier. The V2 Rocket Killstreak is now available. 

In all modes other than War, the V2 Rocket is always equipped for use. "Simply" get 25 non-Scorestreak kills without dying to earn it.
MENU_TUTORIAL_WEAPON_PRESTIGE_DESC: Prestige your weapons to earn the ability to place a Kill Counter or Clan Tag on your favorite gun.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_BOSS_ATTACHMENTS_DESC:
Defeat Undead Bosses in The Tortured Path to unlock unique Boss Attachments for each weapon class! 
Boss Attachments improve weapon performance in new ways to give you a powerful edge against the undead hordes!
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_CUSTOMMATCH: GET IN THE FIGHT - CUSTOM MATCH
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_CUSTOMMATCH_DESC: You can also create Custom Matches to invite up to 3 other players. You will still earn experience while playing in a Custom Match.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_DAILY_WEEKLY_ORDERS_DES: Report to Rideau on a daily basis to receive your orders and get the highest amount of rewards.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_LOOTCHARACTERS_DESC:
You have unlocked a new character by completing Nazi Zombies challenges.

Select your character before selecting Ready Up in order to play as that character in your next match.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_MODS_DESC:
The Elektroschnalle was designed by Doktor Straub to give himself and his living Nazi soldiers an advantage over the undead. The device absorbs the energy released when the undead are killed, and this can be used to open gates, purchase weapons, and grant you exceptional abilities. 

Mods are devices that modify that energy, granting perks and unique attributes to your new abilities.

Unlock more Mods by spending Raven Tokens in the Raven Research menu.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_PUBLICMATCH: GET IN THE FIGHT - PUBLIC MATCH
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_PUBLICMATCH_DESC: Nazi Zombies is best played cooperatively. In Public Match, you will be automatically matched with a team of other online players. By playing, you will start earning experience and unlocking new features.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_READYUP_DESC:
"Ready Up" to select your loadout and mark yourself as ready to start the match. Once all players are ready, the match will start.

Select "Ready Up" now.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_SHATTERED_MATCH_DESC:
Gather your grit as you fight the undead hordes, complete strategic objectives, and possibly, escape with your life!
Survive 10 waves and find a path to extraction to unlock all 3 chapters of The Tortured Path!
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_SHATTERED_RANK: Rank Up and Increase Your Damage!
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_SHATTERED_RANK_DESC:
The Tortured Path introduces a new, dynamic ranking system. As you earn XP and rank up, you'll gain valuable damage boosts that enhance your Zombie slaying power!
But beware, as you grow in power the undead tend to become less predictable!
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_SUPPLIES_VENDOR_DESC:
Stay well stocked as you face the undead hordes!


Visit Rideau regularly to collect Daily and Weekly Orders, Contracts, Payroll and purchase Supply Drops.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_WBK_DESC:
Weapon Build Kits allow you to customize your weapons in Nazi Zombies.

Changing a weapon's kit will change its appearance and configuration when equipped as a starting weapon, or when purchasing it from Weapon Lockers or the Mystery Box.
MENU_TUTORIAL_ZM_WELCOME_DESC:
Begin your tale with the Prologue, and witness the rise of the Final Reich.

Play the Prologue?

MPUI_DESC_MAP_AACHEN: Urban warfare in the Battle of Aachen.  Long range gameplay down the dangerous streets mixed with up-close engagements through war-torn structures.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_BATTLESHIP: Fight on a Battleship at sea near the White Cliffs of Dover.  Long range engagements down the port and starboard with intense close-range fights through ship interiors.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_CANNON_FARM: The massive Gustav railway gun set in the rolling hills of the Crimean Peninsula.  Long range combat opportunities at their most extreme.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_CARENTAN: A remake of the classic map from Call of Duty 2.  Street fighting with plenty of elevated overwatch positions.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_DDAY: D-Day landing site with tight gameplay spaces. Bunkers and trenches create intense close-range battles.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_FLAK_TOWER: German Flak Tower overlooking the skies above Berlin.  Frenetic, close-range battles from end to end.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_FOREST: Battle around a German encampment and vehicle convoy in the snow-covered Ardennes Forest during Battle of the Bulge.  Fast-paced short to medium range engagements.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_FRANCE_VILLAGE: Small French village in Normandy, France - one of the first liberated on D-Day.  Classic combat through streets, and rural outskirts.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_GIBRALTAR_02: Cliff-side fortifications atop the Rock of Gibraltar.  Intense stand-off battles in the center with vertical combat opportunities to the flanks.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_LONDON: Dock-side combat during the Blitz bombing campaign.  Fast paced fighting with mid and longer-range engagements along the docks.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_OLD_SCHOOL_01: A mix of long sights and strategically placed cover makes for a showdown focused on movement and aim.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_OLD_SCHOOL_02: A classic. The building in the center creates a mix of close quarters engagement and long sight lines.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_OLD_SCHOOL_03: Highs and lows. Perches and bridges. A map all about verticality.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_OLD_SCHOOL_HUB: Dash through tall cover to find your enemy first, or post up in an elevated position to try and predict their tactics
MPUI_DESC_MAP_RAID_BULGE: Launch the counter-offensive! This map features 3 fast-paced combat scenarios with short and medium range gameplay.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_RAID_COBRA: Furious battle across a war-torn French village. Features multiple high-intensity combat scenarios involving short and medium range gameplay.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_RAID_D_DAY: Invade or defend Omaha Beach on D-day.
MPUI_DESC_MAP_SCORESTREAK: Specially designed for testing out Scorestreaks

PLATFORM_AIM_GRAPH_DESC:
Adjusts the “feel” when aiming. Maps joystick deflection to turn rate.

Classic – Call of Duty default
Linear – Direct linear response
Slight – Improved low and mid-range control
Balanced – Maximum mid-range control
Extreme – For fine control with absurdly high turn speed settings
PLATFORM_ANISOTROPIC_FILTERING_DESCRIPTI: Improves texture quality of surfaces when viewed at an angle
PLATFORM_ASPECT_RATIO_DESCRIPTION:
The aspect ratio of the game display.  In fullscreen, Auto mode will match the monitor’s aspect ratio while the other modes will letterbox to the specified aspect.  In windowed mode, Auto will allow free scaling of the window while the other modes will restrict the window aspect.



Note: In split-screen, this is the aspect ratio of the entire display and not that of each player view.
PLATFORM_CACHED_SPOT_SHADOWS_DESCRIPTION:
Precalculated spotlight shadow rendering which requires significant additional video memory.

WARNING: Very memory intensive. Only recommended for video cards with at least 4 GB of video memory. Please disable if you experience texture streaming issues that result in blurry textures.
PLATFORM_CACHED_SUN_SHADOWS_DESCRIPTION:
Precalculated sunlight shadow rendering which requires additional video memory.

WARNING: Very memory intensive. Only recommended for video cards with at least 4 GB of video memory. Please disable if you experience texture streaming issues that result in blurry textures.

PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG1: Complete Perk challenges to unlock upgraded Perks.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG10: Edit your Callsign to show off Titles and Emblems you've earned.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG11: Scroll left and right on the Game Summary for more detailed info.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG12: Titles and Emblems you've earned don't reset after entering Prestige Mode.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG13: Shutting down mid-game will cause you to lose your Match Bonus.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG14: Care Package is an airdrop that awards a random killstreak reward.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG15: Tactical Insertion is a flare that marks where your next respawn will be.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG16: Destroy red flares to prevent an enemy Tactical Insertion.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG17: Semtex will stick to your enemy.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG18: The Blast Shield Perk increases your resistance to explosions.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG19: Even when your Heavy Shield is on your back it blocks bullets.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG2: Get Assault and Specialist Killstreak Rewards by getting consecutive kills without dying.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG20: The Heartbeat Sensor attachment detects enemies that are close by.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG21: The Assassin Perk makes you invisible to thermal vision, UAV, Portable Radar, and Heartbeat Sensors.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG22: Hardline makes killstreak rewards require 1 less kill.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG23: You can crawl while in Final Stand.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG24: Recon makes all of your explosive damage paint your enemies to the mini-map, making them easier to find.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG25: The Juiced Deathstreak gives you a limited speed boost when you respawn.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG26: Point your Riot Shield directly at the person shooting you for maximum effectiveness.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG27: Sentry Guns can be temporarily disabled by using Flashbangs or Stun Grenades on them.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG28: The Predator Missile lets you control a missile fired from above.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG29: Crouch with the Riot Shield to cover your feet and get maximum protection.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG3: Earn weapon XP by using your weapon to kill players, destroy equipment, and blow up killstreaks.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG30: Killstreak Rewards are unlocked in the order you choose.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG31: Unlock weapon Proficiencies by leveling up your weapon to get an edge over your opponent.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG32: The default Classes contain items unlocked at later levels, giving you a preview of things to come.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG33: The Scavenger Perk lets you resupply your ammo by taking it from fallen foes.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG34: See the last enemy that killed you with the Revenge Deathstreak.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG35: The Tactical Knife attachment for Handguns speeds up your melee.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG36: The Attachments weapon Proficiency allows you to have 2 attachments on your primary weapon.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG37: Survive a Final Stand bleedout and you stand back up.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG38: Killstreak Rewards attained from airdrop crates do not count towards your killstreak count.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG39: Akimbo weapons give you more firepower but restrict your ability to aim down the sight.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG4: Some killstreak rewards are controllable but leave you vulnerable on the ground.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG40: Give your opponent a C4 surprise with Dead Man's Hand.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG41: Customize each class with its own Strike Package to be ready for any situation that might be thrown at you.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG42: Assault Strike Package items will chain kills to earn the next one.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG43: Be a team player, throw down some Ballistic Vests for your crew.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG44: Hollow Points give you the extra damage needed to get that come back kill.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG46: Once you hear the I.M.S. go off, it's too late.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG47: If you think you need more Perks during battle, you should be using the Specialist Strike Package.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG48: Do you like supporting your team, being on the offensive, or being a lone gun? Strike Packages give you the choice.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG49: The Blind Eye Perk keeps you safe from air support and sentries.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG5: Check out all of your Accolades in the Barracks.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG50: Juggernauts aren't so tough when you cram a missile down their throat.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG51: Use the Stalker Perk to speed you up while strafing an enemy.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG52: The Support Strike Package doesn't reset your killstreak kills when you die.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG53: You have three killstreak slots and one extra slot to store any other killstreaks you get by other means.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG54: Your extra killstreak slot stacks, so you don't need to worry about losing them.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG55: Scroll up and down through your killstreaks and use the one that you want right now.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG6: Use the Sitrep Perk to identify enemy equipment and care package traps.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG7: Swap out Frag grenades for Bouncing Betty, Throwing Knife and other Lethal equipment.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG8: Deathstreaks give you a boost when things aren't going your way.
PLATFORM_DYK_IW5_MSG9: Bullets can ricochet off Riot Shields and kill!

PLATFORM_OPTIONS_NETWORK_ABOUT_NAT_MODER:
Network Address Translation (NAT) is a way to map an entire network to a single IP address. This is a common way of doing networking in most home or work environments.

Your NAT type is Moderate. A Moderate NAT may experience problems connecting to other players who also have Moderate NATs.

The game tried to use UDP port 3074 to open the required port for an open NAT in-game.

Depending on your router, you may be able to enable Universal Plug in Play (UPnP), port forwarding or add your PC to DMZ to get the NAT type to appear Open in game, which will provide the best experience for connecting with other players.

Because of the wide variety of 3rd party routers and unique networking set-ups, Activision cannot offer direct technical support for NAT related issues.

The Call of Duty®: WWII Season Pass gives you access to four exciting DLC packs at one great price, each delivering a collection of new, innovative multiplayer content and more.

With Season Pass you get instant access to the Atlas Gorge Multiplayer Map, a re-envisioning of the fan favorite Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare map, Pipeline.

Explore the map’s new verticality, empowered by Advanced Warfare’s exoskeleton technology, and take control of the devastating map-based turret scorestreak.

Available now.

Visit the in-game store to find out more.

MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_02: We are the most well-trained, physically fit and battle ready unit in the U.S. Army.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_03: Being a sky soldier requires peak physical fitness, mental and emotional toughness, and unhesitating courage.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_04: It doesn't get any more dangerous than this.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_05: We're the first in the fight and we're the last thing the opposition wants to see. We are hunters from the sky.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_06: If you think you've got the guts, then gear up, get on board,
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_AIR_07: And let's go kick some Axis ass.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_02: The sooner we get the introductions out of the way, the sooner we can get to blowing things up.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_03: My name is Major James Parks of The Royal British Armored Division.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_04: Our Armored forces have one mission, and one mission only: engage, and destroy the enemy.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_05: We specialize in direct combat with opposing armored forces, strongpoints, and fighting positions,
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_06: And we are also frequently called on to provide direct fire support for our comrades in the Infantry.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_07: A weapon that is issued in our branch down to the squad level is the light machine gun.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_08: As a member of the Armored Division, it will be your duty to clear the way for your brothers in arms.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_09: If we don't do our job, then they can't do theirs.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_10: We fight for King and country but, most of all, we fight for each other.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_11: It is an honor to be Armored. Never forget that.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_ARM_12: Now let's get started, shall we?
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_02: We do not have the luxury of time as our enemies are closing in, so I will be brief.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_03: We are the pioneers of a new Expeditionary Force, specializing in sabotage and covert operations.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_04: We operate by night, raiding supply points for weapons and explosives.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_05: Including incendiary shotgun shells that spark flames,
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_06: Creating a hailstorm of fire that consumes our enemies.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_07: If you want to join us, you must be willing to sacrifice everything for the good of your countrymen.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_08: We are the French Expeditionary Force.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_09: We are the fire that will burn down the Axis empire to the ground.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_EXP_10: Vive la resistance! Vive la France!
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_01: I am captain John P. Andrews and I'm here to recruit you to the U.S. Army Infantry.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_02: As Infantrymen, you will experience more combat than any other branch in our multi-national force.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_03: You will be the tip of the spear.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_04: For that reason, you will receive individual skills training and be made fit to fight.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_05: The instruction you will receive emphasizes individual rifle marksmanship and hand-to-hand combat,
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_06: So you will be able to engage the enemy at any range.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_07: At longer engagement distances, you will rely on your skills as Infantry riflemen to destroy the enemy.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_08: Up close, you will receive instruction on how to fight with the bayonet.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_09: Sweat in training saves blood in battle.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_10: As long as you have your brothers in arms and your rifle, you are unstoppable.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_INF_11: And if something tries to stop you, show them what a bayonet can do to anything in the way.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_01: Welcome, soldiers, to the Canadian Mountain Division, the most elite unit in the entire Allied armed forces.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_02: If you want to run headlong into Axis strongholds, try the Infantry.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_03: But if you want to make your shot count, then we have a place for you.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_04: You are the eyes of the unit. You take in everything.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_05: The whole world lives between your crosshairs.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_06: Find your vantage point and execute the mission.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_07: They can't hear us - they can't see us. By the time they detect us, it's too late.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_08: If you have a keen eye and a steady hand...
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_09: If you have the patience to wait for the perfect shot...
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_10: If you can quiet the world around you and do what needs to be done...
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_DIV_MOU_11: Then look nowhere else but the Mountain Division.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_01: This is Headquarters, your home away from home and the center of your time here off the front line.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_02: When you're not out there in the field, this is your place to advance your career.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_03: So gear up, train hard, and get to know your fellow soldiers.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_04: We're well-supplied but you've got a lot to learn.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_05: Every man and woman on this beach knows this was just the first step in pushing back the Germans.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_06: We're counting on you to help us push through to the Rhine.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_07: Come on, soldier. Let's get you set up in a Division.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_08: Before heading out to the front, you need to select a division, soldier.
MP_VIDSUBTITLES_FTE_FLY_09: Watch these Division films, and figure out your best way to join the cause.
